        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Hi,\r\n\r\nFrom header returns only the name of the sender when the email address of the sender is like : John Doe <john@domain.net>\r\n\r\nIf i retreive the messages with my email reader, the source of the message contains John Doe <john@domain.net> but Zend_Mail_Storage_Pop3 returns me only 'John Doe'\r\n\r\nThis is the code i'm using.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$mail = new Zend_Mail_Storage_Pop3(array('host'     => $myserver,  'user'     => $myusername,  'password' => $mypassword));\r\n\r\nforeach ($mail as $i => $message) {\r\n    echo \"<hr>MESSAGE $i<hr><pre>\";\r\n\tforeach ($message->getHeaders() as $name => $value) {\r\n\t    if (is_string($value)) {\r\n\t        echo \"$name: $value\\n\";\r\n\t        continue;\r\n\t    }\r\n\t    foreach ($value as $entry) {\r\n\t        echo \"$name: $entry\\n\";\r\n\t    }\r\n\t}\r\n    echo \"<\/pre>\";\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI made the test with different mails servers (including gmail) and i have every times the same result\r\n\r\nRegards\r\n\r\nHJ"
        },
